title: CHIHIRO

description.plain:
“CHIHIRO,” the third track on HIT ME HARD AND SOFT sees Billie feeling unseen and misunderstood as she searches for spiritual and physical reconnection with the world. The title is a reference to the 荻野千尋 (Chihiro “Sen” Ogino), of Spirited Away – an Oscar-winning film from スタジオジブリ (Studio Ghibli) released in 2001 which follows a girl who “learned to face her fears by developing a heightened understanding and appreciation of life.”

During an interview in 2019, Billie professed her love to 宮崎駿 (Hayao Miyazaki)’s filmography (the director of Studio Ghibli) and how she fell in love with the dragon from Spirited Away:

I owe most of [the artistic direction from WHEN WE ALL FALL ASLEEP, WHERE DO WE GO?] to Spirited Away and Miyazaki. Just the way that all that animation is, like No Face…it’s like so “spirit away”…it is so weirdly unrealistic but realistic.

On June 13, 2024, Billie made an Instagram post with a video of her recording “CHIHIRO”. In the caption she states:

nov 17, 2022 making CHIHIRO. had just written this melody & made this video to send to a friend :P

This reveals that she has been working on this track since November 17, 2022 and probably even before that. Both the song and the album it was included on came out on May 17, 2024, one and a half years after its recording process.
